import time
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup as bs
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import google_colab_selenium as gs
from selenium import webdriver
i=0
while i < 100:
    try:
        year = '2018'
        schedule_url = f'https://www.baseball-reference.com/teams/MIN/{year}-schedule-scores.shtml'
        driver = gs.Chrome()
        driver.set_page_load_timeout(15)
        driver.get(schedule_url)
        time.sleep(2)
        driver.execute_script("window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight);")
        time.sleep(2)
        html = driver.page_source
        soup = bs(html, 'html.parser')

        ths = soup.select('#team_schedule > thead > tr > th')
        column_headers = []
        rows = []
        for th in ths:
            column_headers.append(th.text)
        trs = soup.select('#team_schedule > tbody > tr')

        for tr in trs:
            if tr.find(class_='thead'):
                continue
            elif '@' in tr.text:
                continue
            else:
                tds = tr.select('td')
                row = []
                for td in tds:
                    row.append(td.text)
                rows.append(row)
        df = pd.DataFrame(rows, columns=column_headers[1:]).dropna()
    except TimeoutException:
        i += 1
        print(i)
    else:

        i=100

df

while i < 100:
    try:
        year = '2019'
        schedule_url = f'https://www.baseball-reference.com/teams/NYY/{year}-schedule-scores.shtml'
        driver = gs.Chrome()
        driver.set_page_load_timeout(15)
        driver.get(schedule_url)
        time.sleep(2)
        driver.execute_script("window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight);")
        time.sleep(2)
        html = driver.page_source
        soup = bs(html, 'html.parser')

        ths = soup.select('#team_schedule > thead > tr > th')
        column_headers = []
        rows = []
        for th in ths:
            column_headers.append(th.text)
        trs = soup.select('#team_schedule > tbody > tr')

        for tr in trs:
            if tr.find(class_='thead'):
                continue
            elif '@' in tr.text:
                continue
            else:
                tds = tr.select('td')
                row = []
                for td in tds:
                    row.append(td.text)
                rows.append(row)
        yankees_df_2019 = pd.DataFrame(rows, columns=column_headers[1:]).dropna()
    except TimeoutException:
        i += 1
        print(i)
    else:

from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

def create_promotion_regular_boxplots(df, name, season):
    df.Attendance = df.Attendance.astype('str')
    df.Attendance = df.Attendance.str.replace(',', '')
    df.Attendance = df.Attendance.astype('int')
    display(df)
    sns.boxplot(data=df, x='Attendance', y='Promotion', orient='h',).set(title=f'{name} Promotion vs Regular Season Attendance {season}', xlabel='Attendance', ylabel='Promotion')
    plt.show()

def create_promotion_regular_boxplots(df, name, season):
    promo_attendance_list = df[df['Promotion'] == 1]['Attendance'].astype('str').tolist()
    promo_attendance_series = pd.Series([int(x.replace(',', '')) for x in promo_attendance_list])
    regular_attendance_list = df[df['Promotion'] == 0]['Attendance'].astype('str').tolist()
    regular_attendance_series = pd.Series([int(x.replace(',', '')) for x in regular_attendance_list])
    df_output = pd.DataFrame({'Yes': promo_attendance_series, 'No': regular_attendance_series})
    display(df_output)
    sns.boxplot(data=df_output, orient='h').set(title=f'{name} Promotion vs Regular Season Attendance {season}', xlabel='Attendance', ylabel='Promotion')
    plt.show()

def create_4box_promotion_regular_boxplots(df1, df2, df3, df4):

    df2['Mets2019'] = df2.Attendance.astype('str')

    df2['Mets2019'] = df2['Mets2019'].astype('int')
    df3['Yankees2019'] = df3.Attendance.astype('str')

    df3['Yankees2019'] = df3['Yankees2019'].astype('int')
    df4['Twins2018'] = df4.Attendance.astype('str')
    df4['Twins2018'] = df4['Twins2018'].str.replace(',', '')
    df4['Twins2018'] = df4['Twins2018'].astype('int')
    df1 = df1[['Mets2018', 'Promotion']]
    df2 = df2[['Mets2019', 'Promotion']]
    df3 = df3[['Yankees2019', 'Promotion']]
    df4 = df4[['Twins2018', 'Promotion']]

import pandas as pd
from scipy.stats import pearsonr

teams = []
years = []
days = []
correlations = []
t_tests = []
p_values = []

day_teams = []
day_years = []
day_num_ts = {'0':[], '1':[], '2':[], '3': [], '4':[], '5':[], '6':[]}
day_num_ps = {'0':[], '1':[], '2':[], '3': [], '4':[], '5':[], '6':[]}
day_correlations = []

# Set alpha
alpha = 0.05

# Set up each Analysis
df = mets_2018
df['IntDay'] = pd.to_datetime(df.PyDate).dt.dayofweek
l1 = df['Attendance']
l2 = df['IntDay']
team = 'Mets'
year = 2018


# Calculate Pearson Coefficient
corr, _ = pearsonr(l1, l2)
print(f'Pearsons correlation for Attendance vs. Day of Week in {year} for the {team}: %.3f' % corr)
day_teams.append(team)
day_years.append(year)
day_correlations.append(corr)
# Check p_value and t_statistic
for day in range(0,7):
    group1 = df[df.IntDay == day]['Attendance']
    group2 = df[df.IntDay != day]['Attendance']
    t_statistic, p_value = stats.ttest_ind(group1, group2)

    print(f"p value: {p_value}")
    # Check for statistical significance
    if p_value <= alpha:
        print(f"Statistically significant results for Attendance vs. {day} for the {team} in {year}")

    else:
        print(f"Not statistically significant results for Attendance vs. {day} for the {team} in {year}")
        print(f'T-statistic: {t_statistic}')
    print('\n')
    day_num_ts[str(day)].append(t_statistic)
    day_num_ps[str(day)].append(p_value)
l2 = df['Promotion']

# Apply the pearsonr()
corr, _ = pearsonr(l1, l2)
print(f'Pearsons correlation for Attendance vs. Promotion in {year} for the {team}: %.3f' % corr)
# Perform t-test
group1 = df[df.Promotion == 1]['Attendance']
group2 = df[df.Promotion == 0]['Attendance']
t_statistic, p_value = stats.ttest_ind(group1, group2)
teams.append(team)
years.append(year)
correlations.append(corr)
t_tests.append(t_statistic)
p_values.append(p_value)
print(f"p value: {p_value}")
# Check for statistical significance
if p_value <= alpha:
    print(f"Statistically significant results for Attendance vs. Promotion for the {team} in {year}")
else:
    print(f"Not statistically significant results for Attendance vs. Promotion for the {team} in {year}")
print('\n')
print('\n')

def set_background_color(df):
    ret = pd.DataFrame('', index=df.index, columns=df.columns)
    for row in df.itertuples():
        print(row)
        if row[4] < 0.05:
            ret.loc[row.Index, 'Monday p value'] = 'background-color: green'
        if row[5] < 0.05:
            ret.loc[row.Index, 'Tuesday p value'] = 'background-color: green'
        if row[6] < 0.05:
            ret.loc[row.Index, 'Wednesday p value'] = 'background-color: green'
        if row[7] < 0.05:
            ret.loc[row.Index, 'Thursday p value'] = 'background-color: green'
        if row[8] < 0.05:
            ret.loc[row.Index, 'Friday p value'] = 'background-color: green'
        if row[9] < 0.05:
            ret.loc[row.Index, 'Saturday p value'] = 'background-color: green'
        if row[10] < 0.05:
            ret.loc[row.Index, 'Sunday p value'] = 'background-color: green'
    print(ret)
    return ret

def create_4box_promotion_regular_boxplots_day(df1, df2, df3, df4):
    df1['Mets2018'] = df1.Attendance.astype('str')
    df1['Mets2018'] = df1['Mets2018'].str.replace(',', '')
    df1['Mets2018'] = df1['Mets2018'].astype('int')
    df2['Mets2019'] = df2.Attendance.astype('str')
    df2['Mets2019'] = df2['Mets2019'].str.replace(',', '')
    df2['Mets2019'] = df2['Mets2019'].astype('int')
    df3['Yankees2019'] = df3.Attendance.astype('str')
    df3['Yankees2019'] = df3['Yankees2019'].str.replace(',', '')
    df3['Yankees2019'] = df3['Yankees2019'].astype('int')
    df4['Twins2018'] = df4.Attendance.astype('str')
    df4['Twins2018'] = df4['Twins2018'].str.replace(',', '')
    df4['Twins2018'] = df4['Twins2018'].astype('int')
    df1 = df1[['Mets2018', 'Promotion','Day']]
    df2 = df2[['Mets2019', 'Promotion','Day']]
    df3 = df3[['Yankees2019', 'Promotion','Day']]
    df4 = df4[['Twins2018', 'Promotion','Day']]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(2,2)
    fig.set_size_inches(8, 8)
    plt.subplots_adjust(wspace=0.5, hspace=0.5)
    df1Y = df1[(df1['Promotion'] == 1) & (df1['Day'] == 'Monday')].Mets2018.tolist()
    df1N = df1[df1['Promotion'] == 0].Mets2018.tolist()
    df1YN = [df1Y, df1N]
    df2Y = df2[df2['Promotion'] == 1].Mets2019.tolist()
    df2N = df2[df2['Promotion'] == 0].Mets2019.tolist()
    df2YN = [df2Y, df2N]
    df3Y = df3[df3['Promotion'] == 1].Yankees2019.tolist()
    df3N = df3[df3['Promotion'] == 0].Yankees2019.tolist()
    df3YN = [df3Y, df3N]
    df4Y = df4[df4['Promotion'] == 1].Twins2018.tolist()
    df4N = df4[df4['Promotion'] == 0].Twins2018.tolist()
    df4YN = [df4Y, df4N]
    print(df1YN)
    acolors = ['#002D72', '#FF5910']
    ccolors = ['#C4CED3', '#0C2340']
    dcolors = ['#002B5C', '#D31145']
    aplot = ax[0,0].boxplot(df1YN, tick_labels=['Yes', 'No'], patch_artist=True)
    ax[0,0].set(title=f'Mets 2018', ylabel='Attendance', xlabel='Promotion')
    bplot = ax[1,0].boxplot(df2YN, tick_labels=['Yes', 'No'], patch_artist=True)
    ax[1,0].set(title=f'Mets 2019', ylabel='Attendance', xlabel='Promotion')
    cplot = ax[0,1].boxplot(df3YN, tick_labels=['Yes', 'No'], patch_artist=True)
    ax[0,1].set(title=f'Yankees 2019', ylabel='Attendance', xlabel='Promotion')
    dplot = ax[1,1].boxplot(df4YN, tick_labels=['Yes', 'No'], patch_artist=True)
    ax[1,1].set(title=f'Twins 2018', ylabel='Attendance', xlabel='Promotion')
    for patch, color in zip(aplot['boxes'], acolors):
        patch.set_facecolor(color)
    for patch, color in zip(bplot['boxes'], acolors):
        patch.set_facecolor(color)
    for patch, color in zip(cplot['boxes'], ccolors):
        patch.set_facecolor(color)

    for patch, color in zip(dplot['boxes'], dcolors):
        patch.set_facecolor(color)

    # sns.boxplot(data=df).set(title=f'Promotion vs Regular Season Attendance', xlabel='Attendance', ylabel='Promotion')
    plt.suptitle('Promotion vs Regular Season Attendance', y=0.95)
    plt.show()
